data.description: La Habra Heights Mid Century Estate! This unique property is located on a private cul-de-sac and is surrounded by 80 fruit trees with amazing views. Large family room with vaulted ceilings has two walls of windows. Completely redone modern chefs kitchen looks out on to the Southern California skyline. Kitchen includes two sinks a gas cook top, wall convection oven, built in microwave, counter top steamer, built in coffee maker, cook top pot filler, dishwasher, wine fridge & SubZero fridge. Tons of cabinet and counter space. Kitchen leads out to a balcony that over looks the property. Laundry room (with gas dryer hook ups) located off the hall way with generous linen and storage closets. Master bedroom has a pristinely preserved vintage bathroom with a walk in closet that includes a custom dressing/make up table. Secondary bedroom / den has built in cabinets and a large closet. Full bathroom off the hall way services the secondary bedroom and guests. Finished off storage area under the house. Large covered patio space located off the living room and kitchen that is an amazing space for relaxing and entertaining large groups. Sonos sound system is wired throughout the house and patio space. TV's included in the kitchen dining space and secondary bedroom. Bamboo and Marmoleum flooring throughout. All renovations have been done with eco-friendly materials. This home has been lovingly cared for and designed to create a restful home space.
